All Classes and Interfaces

Class
Description
authtoken
Auth token object has the users random generated token with the username property to pair with the token
AuthtokenDAO
This is the abstraction for the Authtoken table, only component that interfaces with the authToken table
ClearRequest
Deletes ALL data from the database, including user, authToken, persona and event data The request body is empty
ClearResponse
This class will contain our message and our boolean value indicating whether request was successful
ClearService
This clears the data from all the databases using the /clear webAPI
DataAccessError
if there is a SQL error this object will be thrown
Database
Handles the connection
Event
 
EventDAO
This class interfaces with the database, it can query, update, remove, or drop
EventRequest
without any additional parameters, it returns ALL family members of the current user.
EventResponse
Returns potential response or error of the event request
EventService
This will execute the /event webAPI
FillRequest
Populates the server's database with generated data for the specified username.
FillResponse
Will have success or error message
FillService
This will execute the /fill/ webAPI for the specified user
LoadRequest
Clears all data from the database (just like the /clear API) Loads the user, person, and event data from the request body into the database.
LoadResponse
Returns the success response body or error response body
LoadService
This will execute the /load webAPI
LoginRequest
Logs the user in Returns an authtoken.
LoginResponse
This will contain a response success or error
LoginService
This will carry out the /user/login webAPI
Person
 
PersonDAO
PersonDAO is the abstract interface that interacts explicitly with the person table
PersonRequest
Returns ALL family members of the current user.
PersonResponse
Response body will have a success content or error
PersonService
This will carre out the webAPI of /person/ and its optional ID parameter
RegisterRequest
Creates a new user account (user row in the database) Generates 4 generations of ancestor data for the new user (just like the /fill endpoint if called with a generations value of 4 and this new user’s username as parameters) Logs the user in Returns an authtoken
RegisterResponse
Will have success response or error
RegisterService
THis will carry out the /user/register webAPI
ServerTest
This is a mock client used for pass off of the CS240 Family Map Server project.

UserDAO
User Data access object interfaces only with the user table, it contains function that manipulate the user table for in our database.
